{"questionId":"9066661","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bromine and methanoic acid react in aqueous solution.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Br<sub>2</sub> (aq) + HCOOH (aq) → 2Br<sup>−</sup> (aq) + 2H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + CO<sub>2</sub> (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The reaction was monitored by measuring the volume of carbon dioxide produced as time<br>progressed.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/678d23bae9495ae4a3337049953f74911a3c8d7b.png\" width=\"701\" height=\"486\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine from the graph the rate of reaction at 20 s, in cm<sup>3</sup> s<sup>−1</sup>, showing your working.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">tangent drawn to curve at t = 20 s&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">slope/gradient calculation&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">0.35 «cm<sup>3</sup> s<sup>–1</sup>»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept values in the range 0.32–0.42&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\">«cm</span><sup style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:11.6px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">3</sup><span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\"> s</span><sup style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:11.6px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">–1</sup><span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\">»&nbsp;</span></span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066661","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine from the graph the rate of reaction at 20 s, in cm3 s−1, showing your working.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Chemical kinetics","6.1 Collision theory and rates of reaction","Core","Topic 6: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}